{"title_page": "Ibrahim Muhammed Kirikasama", "text_new": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox Officeholder\n| name                = Ibrahim Mohammed Kirikasama\n| image               = Ibrahim Mohammed Kirikasama.png\n| width               = 112px\n| office1             = Senator of the Federal Republic of Nigeria from [[Jigawa State]] North East District\n| term_start1         = 29 May 1999\n| term_end1           = 29 May 2007\n| predecessor1        = \n| successor1          = [[Abdulaziz Usman]]\n| birth_date          = February 1952\n| birth_place         = [[Kiri Kasama]] LGA, [[Jigawa State]], [[Nigeria]]\n| death_date          = \n| party               = [[All Nigeria People's Party]]\n| nationality         = [[Nigerian]]\n}}\n\n'''Ibrahim Mohammed Kirikasama'''<ref>[[Kiri Kasama|Kirikasama]] is the name of the community into which Ibrahim Mohammed was born.</ref> (born February 1952) was elected Senator for the Jigawa North East constituency of [[Jigawa State]], [[Nigeria]] at the start of the [[Nigerian Fourth Republic]], running on the [[All People's Party (Nigeria)|All People's Party]] (APP) platform. He took office on 29 May 1999.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://psephos.adam-carr.net/countries/n/nigeria/nigerialeg2.txt\n |title=FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF NIGERIA LEGISLATIVE ELECTION OF 20 FEBRUARY AND 7 MARCH 1999\n |work=Psephos\n |accessdate=2010-06-21}}</ref>\nHe was reelected in April 2003 on the [[All Nigeria People's Party]] (ANPP) platform for a second four-year term.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.dawodu.com/senator.htm\n |title=Senators\n |work=Dawodu\n |accessdate=2010-06-21}}</ref>\n \nAfter taking his seat in the Senate in June 1999 he was appointed to committees on Labour, Women Affairs, Agriculture, Information and Social Development & Sports.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.nigeriacongress.org/assembly/committees1.htm \n |title=Congressional Committees \n |publisher=Nigeria Congress \n |accessdate=2010-06-21 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091118151316/http://www.nigeriacongress.org/assembly/committees1.htm \n |archivedate=18 November 2009 \n |df=dmy-all \n}}</ref>\nHis constituency contains the ecologically and economically important wetlands on the [[Hadejia River]], threatened by changes to water release due to the upriver [[Tiga Dam]].<ref>\n{{cite web\n |url=http://www.brad.ac.uk/acad/des/seminar/water/seminar5/papers/10_Hassan_Bdliya.pdf\n |title=Institutional Failures in the Management of Critical Water Resources: The Case of the Komadugu-Yobe Basin in Nigeria\n |date=21 February 2006\n |author1=Hassan H. Bdliya\n |author2=Julian Barr\n |author3=Steve Fraser\n |accessdate=2010-06-21\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110613101004/http://www.brad.ac.uk/acad/des/seminar/water/seminar5/papers/10_Hassan_Bdliya.pdf\n |archive-date=13 June 2011\n |url-status=dead\n |df=dmy-all\n }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.thisdayonline.com/archive/2004/08/03/20040803est02.html \n |title=Sand Dunes Overrun Northern Settlements, Advance Southwards \n |work=ThisDay \n |date=2004-08-03 \n |accessdate=2010-06-21 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050126041942/http://www.thisdayonline.com/archive/2004/08/03/20040803est02.html \n |archivedate=26 January 2005 \n |df=dmy-all \n}}</ref>\nIn a May 2006 debate on the proposal to allow President [[Olusegun Obasanjo]] to run for a third term of office, Kirikasama opposed the proposal, describing it as an attempt at \"legalising the illegality and constitutionalising unconstitutionality\".<ref>\n{{cite web\n |url=http://www.sunnewsonline.com/webpages/news/national/2006/may/12/national-12-05-2006-003.htm\n |title=Senators knock out third term \u2022 44 against, 39 for \u2022 21 reps for, 18 against\n |author1=BASHIR UMAR\n |author2=JAMES OJO\n |author3=RAZAQ BAMIDELE\n |work=Daily Sun\n |date=12 May 2006\n |accessdate=2010-06-21\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070805034326/http://www.sunnewsonline.com/webpages/news/national/2006/may/12/national-12-05-2006-003.htm\n |archive-date=5 August 2007\n |url-status=dead\n |df=dmy-all\n }}\n</ref>\n\nIn the April 2007 elections, Kirikasama ran for governor of Jigawa State on the ANPP platform, but was defeated by Alhaji [[Sule Lamido]] on the [[People's Democratic Party (Nigeria)|People's Democratic Party]] by 523,940 votes to 260,055.<ref>{{cite web\n |url        = http://www.thesourceng.com/partyresultapril30.htm\n |date       = 30 April 2007\n |title      = How The Parties Fared\n |work       = The Source Magazine\n |accessdate = 2010-06-21\n}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\nHis selection as candidate had been resisted by the state chapter of the ANPP.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/article-1G1-159371242/caucus-rejects-anpp-guber.html\n |title=Caucus Rejects ANPP Guber Flag Bearer in Jigawa.\n |work=Vanguard\n |date=15 February 2007 \n |author=Abdulsalam Muhammad\n |accessdate=2010-06-21}}</ref> \nKirikasama said he would not challenge Lamido's victory for \"personal reasons\".<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.pointblanknews.com/artopn606.html\n |author=Michael Egbejumi-David\n |work=Point Blank News\n |title=Election Tribunals\u2019 Update 2: 1st August 2008\n |accessdate=2010-06-21}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Nigerian Senators of the 4th National Assembly}}\n{{Nigerian Senators of the 5th National Assembly}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kirikasama, Ibrahim Mohammed}}\n[[Category:Members of the Senate (Nigeria)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Jigawa State]]\n[[Category:All People's Party (Nigeria) politicians]]\n[[Category:All Nigeria Peoples Party politicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Nigerian politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nigerian politicians]]\n\n\n{{Nigeria-politician-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{EngvarB|date=January 2014}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2014}}\n{{Infobox Officeholder\n| name                = Ibrahim Mohammed Kirikasama\n| image               = Ibrahim Mohammed Kirikasama.png\n| width               = 112px\n| office1             = Senator of the Federal Republic of Nigeria from [[Jigawa State]] North East District\n| term_start1         = 29 May 1999\n| term_end1           = 29 May 2007\n| predecessor1        = \n| successor1          = [[Abdulaziz Usman]]\n| birth_date          = February 1952\n| birth_place         = [[Kiri Kasama]] LGA, [[Jigawa State]], [[Nigeria]]\n| death_date          = \n| party               = [[All Nigeria People's Party]]\n| nationality         = [[Nigerian]]\n}}\n\n'''Ibrahim Mohammed Kirikasama'''<ref>[[Kiri Kasama|Kirikasama]] is the name of the community into which Ibrahim Mohammed was born.</ref> (born February 1952) was elected Senator for the Jigawa North East constituency of [[Jigawa State]], [[Nigeria]] at the start of the [[Nigerian Fourth Republic]], running on the [[All People's Party (Nigeria)|All People's Party]] (APP) platform. He took office on 29 May 1999.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://psephos.adam-carr.net/countries/n/nigeria/nigerialeg2.txt\n |title=FEDERAL REPUBLIC OF NIGERIA LEGISLATIVE ELECTION OF 20 FEBRUARY AND 7 MARCH 1999\n |work=Psephos\n |accessdate=2010-06-21}}</ref>\nHe was reelected in April 2003 on the [[All Nigeria People's Party]] (ANPP) platform for a second four-year term.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.dawodu.com/senator.htm\n |title=Senators\n |work=Dawodu\n |accessdate=2010-06-21}}</ref>\n \nAfter taking his seat in the Senate in June 1999 he was appointed to committees on Labour, Women Affairs, Agriculture, Information and Social Development & Sports.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.nigeriacongress.org/assembly/committees1.htm \n |title=Congressional Committees \n |publisher=Nigeria Congress \n |accessdate=2010-06-21 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20091118151316/http://www.nigeriacongress.org/assembly/committees1.htm \n |archivedate=18 November 2009 \n |df=dmy-all \n}}</ref>\nHis constituency contains the ecologically and economically important wetlands on the [[Hadejia River]], threatened by changes to water release due to the upriver [[Tiga Dam]].<ref>\n{{cite web\n |url=http://www.brad.ac.uk/acad/des/seminar/water/seminar5/papers/10_Hassan_Bdliya.pdf\n |title=Institutional Failures in the Management of Critical Water Resources: The Case of the Komadugu-Yobe Basin in Nigeria\n |date=21 February 2006\n |author1=Hassan H. Bdliya\n |author2=Julian Barr\n |author3=Steve Fraser\n |accessdate=2010-06-21\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110613101004/http://www.brad.ac.uk/acad/des/seminar/water/seminar5/papers/10_Hassan_Bdliya.pdf\n |archive-date=13 June 2011\n |url-status=dead\n |df=dmy-all\n }}\n</ref><ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.thisdayonline.com/archive/2004/08/03/20040803est02.html \n |title=Sand Dunes Overrun Northern Settlements, Advance Southwards \n |work=ThisDay \n |date=2004-08-03 \n |accessdate=2010-06-21 \n |url-status=dead \n |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20050126041942/http://www.thisdayonline.com/archive/2004/08/03/20040803est02.html \n |archivedate=26 January 2005 \n |df=dmy-all \n}}</ref>\nIn a May 2006 debate on the proposal to allow President [[Olusegun Obasanjo]] to run for a third term of office, Kirikasama opposed the proposal, describing it as an attempt at \"legalising the illegality and constitutionalising unconstitutionality\".<ref>\n{{cite web\n |url=http://www.sunnewsonline.com/webpages/news/national/2006/may/12/national-12-05-2006-003.htm\n |title=Senators knock out third term \u2022 44 against, 39 for \u2022 21 reps for, 18 against\n |author1=BASHIR UMAR\n |author2=JAMES OJO\n |author3=RAZAQ BAMIDELE\n |work=Daily Sun\n |date=12 May 2006\n |accessdate=2010-06-21\n |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070805034326/http://www.sunnewsonline.com/webpages/news/national/2006/may/12/national-12-05-2006-003.htm\n |archive-date=5 August 2007\n |url-status=dead\n |df=dmy-all\n }}\n</ref>\n\nIn the April 2007 elections, Kirikasama ran for governor of Jigawa State on the ANPP platform, but was defeated by Alhaji [[Sule Lamido]] on the [[People's Democratic Party (Nigeria)|People's Democratic Party]] by 523,940 votes to 260,055.<ref>{{cite web\n |url        = http://www.thesourceng.com/partyresultapril30.htm\n |date       = 30 April 2007\n |title      = How The Parties Fared\n |work       = The Source Magazine\n |accessdate = 2010-06-21\n}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\nHis selection as candidate had been resisted by the state chapter of the ANPP.<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.accessmylibrary.com/article-1G1-159371242/caucus-rejects-anpp-guber.html\n |title=Caucus Rejects ANPP Guber Flag Bearer in Jigawa.\n |work=Vanguard\n |date=15 February 2007 \n |author=Abdulsalam Muhammad\n |accessdate=2010-06-21}}</ref> \nKirikasama said he would not challenge Lamido\u2019s victory for \"personal reasons\".<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.pointblanknews.com/artopn606.html\n |author=Michael Egbejumi-David\n |work=Point Blank News\n |title=Election Tribunals\u2019 Update 2: 1st August 2008\n |accessdate=2010-06-21}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n{{Nigerian Senators of the 4th National Assembly}}\n{{Nigerian Senators of the 5th National Assembly}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kirikasama, Ibrahim Mohammed}}\n[[Category:Members of the Senate (Nigeria)]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:1952 births]]\n[[Category:Jigawa State]]\n[[Category:All People's Party (Nigeria) politicians]]\n[[Category:All Nigeria Peoples Party politicians]]\n[[Category:20th-century Nigerian politicians]]\n[[Category:21st-century Nigerian politicians]]\n\n\n{{Nigeria-politician-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: \u2019s \u2192 's", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/w